[normal]ensuring that public services[bold] are accountable to the people who use them, and to elected officials?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Question [bold]5. How successful have the Government’s reforms been in opening up public services to grassroots community groups rather than to large [bold]private or third sector organisations?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Question [bold]6. How well do different tiers of government or different parts of single public [bold]sector organisation[bold]s[bold], at central, local authority or district councils level, work together to deliver public services?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Question [bold]7. What examples are there of innovative ways to deliver better public services, from other countries or from other public service providers?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
